President Cyril Ramaphosa has announced Advocate Shamila Batohi as the new head of the National Prosecuting Authority. Batohi thanked Ramaphosa for having confidence in her to lead the NPA. "Today, your NDPP stands with you and together we stand for justice and the nation," Batohi said. Batohi said that she will serve the country with humility and dedication. "This is a historic moment for women," said Batohi. 